However, they are mapped directly from `client_id` and `opportunity_ref` respectively from the `project` source table without any validation or handling for potentially NULL values from the source. If `project.client_id` or `project.opportunity_ref` can be NULL, these target columns will violate their NOT NULL constraint. They should be handled with `COALESCE` to provide a meaningful default or a placeholder ID if a source value is missing.'}])
