2026-07-04 16:35:31 [plan_write_critique] critique_round_complete (verdicts=[{'target_table': 'Account', 'verdict': 'needs_revision', 'comments': "Id: The target 'Id' column is 'text NOT NULL'. The expression 'MD5(TRIM(kunden_nr))::uuid' casts the MD5 hash (a text string) to a UUID type. While PostgreSQL implicitly converts this back to text for the output column, it formats it with hyphens. For cross-table consistency with foreign key ID generations in other models (e.g., Contact.AccountId, Opportunity.AccountId, Installed_Asset__c.Account__c) which typically produce non-hyphenated MD5 hashes, it's recommended to remove the '::uuid' cast and directly use 'MD5(TRIM(kunden_nr))'. This ensures all IDs derived from a source key have the same textual representation across tables."}, {'target_table': 'Contact', 'verdict': 'needs_revision', 'comments': "AccountId: The 'AccountId' is generated as 'MD5(k.kunden_nr)' (producing a non-hyphenated MD5 hash). This will not consistently match the 'Id' in the 'Account' table, which is currently generated with 'MD5(...)::uuid' (producing a hyphenated UUID string). To ensure cross-table consistency, 'AccountId' must match the exact string format of 'Account.Id'. It is recommended to standardize all generated IDs to be non-hyphenated MD5 hashes by removing '::uuid' casts across all models where 'Id' is a text column."}, {'target_table': 'Installed_Asset__c', 'verdict': 'needs_revision', 'comments': "Account__c: The 'Account__c' is generated as 'MD5(kunden.kunden_nr)' (non-hyphenated). This will not consistently match the 'Id' in the 'Account' table (currently hyphenated). Revision is needed to ensure 'Account__c' matches 'Account.Id' consistently.\nProject__c: The 'Project__c' is generated as 'MD5(proj.proj_id)' (non-hyphenated). This will not consistently match the 'Id' in the 'Project__c' table (currently hyphenated). Revision is needed to ensure 'Project__c' matches 'Project__c.Id' consistently.\nIt is recommended to standardize all generated IDs to be non-hyphenated MD5 hashes by removing '::uuid' casts across all models where 'Id' or foreign key IDs are text columns."}, {'target_table': 'Opportunity', 'verdict': 'needs_revision', 'comments': "AccountId: The 'AccountId' is generated as 'MD5(chancen.kd_nr)::TEXT' (effectively non-hyphenated). This will not consistently match the 'Id' in the 'Account' table (currently hyphenated). Revision is needed to ensure 'AccountId' matches 'Account.Id' consistently.\nCreatedDate, LastModifiedDate: The format 'YYYY-MM-DD HH24:MI:SS.US' is used, which is inconsistent with the 'YYYY-MM-DD HH24:MI:SS' format used in the 'Account' and 'Installed_Asset__c' models, and 'YYYY-MM-DD' in 'Contact'. While all are valid text, for better consistency across system-generated date fields, it's recommended to standardize to a single format like 'YYYY-MM-DD HH24:MI:SS'."}, {'target_table': 'Project__c', 'verdict': 'needs_revision', 'comments': "Id: The target 'Id' column is 'text NOT NULL'. The expression 'MD5(p.proj_id)::uuid' produces a hyphenated UUID string. For cross-table consistency and adherence to the 'text' type of the target column, it's recommended to remove the '::uuid' cast and directly use 'MD5(p.proj_id)' to produce a non-hyphenated MD5 hash.\nAccount__c: The 'Account__c' is generated as 'MD5(k.kunden_nr)::uuid' (hyphenated). This will not consistently match the 'Id' in the 'Account' table if it's revised to be non-hyphenated, and it is inconsistent with 'AccountId' in 'Contact', 'Opportunity', and 'Installed_Asset__c'. Revision is needed.\nOpportunity__c: The 'Opportunity__c' is generated as 'MD5(c.chance_id)::uuid' (hyphenated). This will not consistently match the 'Id' in the 'Opportunity' table, which uses 'MD5(...)::TEXT' (non-hyphenated). Revision is needed.\nCreatedDate, LastModifiedDate: The format 'YYYY-MM-DD HH24:MI:SS.US' is used, which is inconsistent with other models. For better consistency, it's recommended to standardize to 'YYYY-MM-DD HH24:MI:SS'.\nOverall, it is critical to standardize all generated IDs (both primary and foreign keys) to be non-hyphenated MD5 hashes by removing '::uuid' casts across all models where 'Id' or foreign key IDs are text columns to ensure cross-table referential integrity."}])
